arts.ttl: Man City sign Frankfurt forward Marmoush for £59m
arts.sum: Egypt forward Omar Marmoush, the second highest scorer in the Bundesliga this season, has agreed a contract until 2029.

arts.ttl: Uzun and Eketiké strike as Frankfurt soar past Ferencváros
arts.sum: Eintracht Frankfurt welcomed the arrival of Ferencváros tonight for Matchday 7 of the Europa League where Die Adler ran out 2-0 winners.

arts.ttl: Eintracht Frankfurt target Elye Wahi for €20m, medical set for Friday
arts.sum: Sky and Kicker are currently reporting that Elye Wahi’s transfer to Eintracht Frankfurt is set to be confirmed tomorrow.

arts.ttl: Kaiserslautern pick up attackers Grant-Leon Ranos and Faride Alidou
arts.sum: Borussia Mönchengladbach confirmed a loan out for young Armenian attacker Grant-Leon Ranos late Wednesday. Ranos' new second division side, 1. FC Kaiserslautern, then confirmed a pick up of another player from a Bundesliga club on Thursday.

arts.ttl: Confirmed Lineups: Eintracht Frankfurt vs. Ferencváros
arts.sum: Official team news has just been released for Die Adler who host Ferencváros for Matchday 7 of the UEFA Europa League.

arts.sum: Marseille centre-forward Elye Wahi (22) is edging closer to joining Eintracht Frankfurt as both clubs have reportedly reached an agreement, L’Equipe understands. The France U21 international is set to leave…

arts.ttl: Eintracht Frankfurt increase offer for Elye Wahi as agreement with Marseille nears
arts.sum: Elye Wahi (22) is nearing a move away from Olympique de Marseille, just six months after joining the club, according to a report from Fabrizio Romano. Wahi joined OM from RC…

arts.ttl: Marseille turn down first Frankfurt bid for potential Marmoush replacement
arts.sum: According to Sky Germany, Eintracht Frankfurt's first bid for Elye Wahi has been rejected by Olympique Marseille.
